        <p>We tested 10 review management tools across 90 days on 14 local business profiles. Here is the ranking by what each tool actually generates, response time on negative reviews, and where the per-location price stops being worth it.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-tldr">
          <div class="callout-label">⚡ TL;DR — Pick by your business size and channel</div>
          <p><strong>You want an all-in-one platform:</strong> Birdeye ($229+/mo). <strong>You want SMS-driven generation:</strong> Podium. <strong>You want affordable small business automation:</strong> NiceJob ($79/mo). <strong>You want enterprise multi-location:</strong> Reputation.com. <strong>You want reviews + local SEO done-for-you:</strong> theStacc Local SEO ($49/mo).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Want reviews handled as part of local SEO — not a separate tool?</h4>
            <p>theStacc Local SEO covers review monitoring, response support, citations, weekly GBP posts, and rank tracking. <strong>From $49/mo — one bill instead of Birdeye + a citation tool.</strong></p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">See a live demo <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">No card · 15-min walkthrough</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="what-is">Why review management tools matter</h2>
        <p>Review tools solve four overlapping jobs. Pick by which one is hurting your business most:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Review generation</strong> — SMS or email requests after each transaction.</li>
          <li><strong>Review monitoring</strong> — alerts across Google, Yelp, Facebook, industry platforms.</li>
          <li><strong>Review response</strong> — reply to every review within 48 hours, ideally inside the tool.</li>
          <li><strong>Sentiment analytics</strong> — what customers are saying, theme by theme.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">⚠️ The negative review trap</div>
          <p>Most businesses panic-shop for review tools <strong>after a 1-star review tanks their average.</strong> By then it's too late — generating enough new positive reviews to dilute a 1-star takes weeks. The right time to set up review automation is in month 1 of your local SEO, not month 12 after damage.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="how-we-tested">How we tested all 10 review tools</h2>
        <p>Same 14 business profiles, same 90-day window, same review request volume — April through June 2026.</p>

        <ul>
